			<h3 ><a href="#p79086">Re: External Battery Charger Accessory</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=79086&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61#p79086"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1184&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61">mfortuna</a></strong> &raquo; June 1st, 2010, 7:46 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">They show up on <a href="http://www.robotreviews.com/cgi-bin/jump/jump.cgi?21" class="th23autolinks postlink" onclick="this.target='_blank';" rel="nofollow">ebay</a> from time to time. They are getting rare since it has been out of production for quite some time.<br /><br />Another way to do it would be to charge both batteries in the roomba and then run two missions, allowing the robot to cool off between.</div>

