	<div id="p81873" class="post bg2">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p81873">Re: External Battery Charger Accessory</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=81873&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61#p81873"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1074&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61">vic7767</a></strong> &raquo; August 23rd, 2010, 12:35 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">No,  using a stock automotive battery charger to charge a Roomba battery is not a good idea.  Look for a Roomba Rapid Charger instead.  If you use a stock charger that does not monitor the built-in thermistor of the Roomba battery then be sure and stick around during charging to disconnect the battery if issues develop.</div>

			<div id="sig81873" class="signature"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #FF0000">Roomba and Neato Mods</span>, come visit:  <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.vic7767.com/" onclick="this.target='_blank';" rel="nofollow">http://www.vic7767.com/</a><!-- m --></span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #008000"> <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.Robot-Doc.com/" onclick="this.target='_blank';" rel="nofollow">http://www.Robot-Doc.com/</a><!-- m --></span></span></div>

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile81873">
