			<h3 ><a href="#p81876">Re: External Battery Charger Accessory</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=81876&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61#p81876"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12281&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61">TechGuy</a></strong> &raquo; August 23rd, 2010, 1:20 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>Nitrowing wrote:</cite>Is this because a car charger outputs too much amps?<br />Sticking around for a couple of hours watching a battery, not knowing what to look for??! Ummm....</div></blockquote><br /><br />Roomba charge the battery around 1.3A and also monitor the battery temperature.  Heat kills battery.  Roomba will switch to trickle charging mode after full charge by monitor the dV (I think - correct me if I am wrong).<br /><br />A car charger may use too much current and heat up the battery too much too fast.</div>

			<div id="sig81876" class="signature"><span style="font-weight: bold">Charging battery directly:</span> <a href="http://www.robotreviews.com/chat/viewtopic.php?f=1&amp;t=13212" class="postlink-local">400 Series,</a> <a href="http://www.robotreviews.com/chat/viewtopic.php?f=1&amp;t=12690" class="postlink-local">500 Series,</a>. How to <a href="http://www.robotreviews.com/chat/viewtopic.php?f=1&amp;t=11053&amp;start=240#p92473" class="postlink-local">Desolder</a><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">For Sale:</span>  <a href="http://www.ebay.ca/itm/191159269044?ssPageName=STRK:MESELX:IT&amp;_trksid=p3984.m1555.l2649" class="postlink" onclick="this.target='_blank';" rel="nofollow">Black CHM 2 Ball Bearings set</a></div>

		</div>

		
