			<h3 ><a href="#p81881">Re: External Battery Charger Accessory</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=81881&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61#p81881"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1184&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61">mfortuna</a></strong> &raquo; August 23rd, 2010, 1:48 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">There are Radio Control grade chargers that can charge a 4S Li-ION or 12 cell NIMH/NICAD pack from a 12V supply. You can get a cheap PC supply that puts out 12V and use it to run the charger. Total investment can approach $100 though. I have had good luck with this charger:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www3.towerhobbies.com/cgi-bin/wti0001p?&amp;I=LXMAH9&amp;P=ML" onclick="this.target='_blank';" rel="nofollow">http://www3.towerhobbies.com/cgi-bin/wt ... XMAH9&amp;P=ML</a><!-- m --></div>

