			<h3 ><a href="#p81887">Re: External Battery Charger Accessory</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=81887&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61#p81887"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1184&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61">mfortuna</a></strong> &raquo; August 23rd, 2010, 4:10 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">If your supply is only putting out 14.72V then you probably will not fully charge the pack. That may be why it is not getting warm. Once the pack gets to 14.72V no current will flow. Most NIMHs and NICADs tend to peak near 1.5V which is 18V per pack.</div>

			<div id="sig81887" class="signature">Mike<br />Reds x 3, Dirt Dog, Disco (now a parts bot), Create, Scooba 350, and Security Dawg<br />Evolution Mint<br />Neato XV-11</div>

