			<h3 ><a href="#p81905">Re: External Battery Charger Accessory</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=81905&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61#p81905"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7512&amp;sid=9144880458ee87a9ea9f6797a9f88b61">Nudnik</a></strong> &raquo; August 23rd, 2010, 10:42 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">I wonder if a laptop power adapter would work. For example my HP adapter has 19 volt output, and there are generic versions on <a href="http://www.robotreviews.com/cgi-bin/jump/jump.cgi?21" class="th23autolinks postlink" onclick="this.target='_blank';" rel="nofollow">Ebay</a> at low cost.<br /><br />Adam</div>

			<div id="sig81905" class="signature">Roomba 562 and 2 cats</div>

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile81905">
